{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"30a663e6-24eb-4fda-9b72-3e6b663e889d","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter updating, run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nAlso check for any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) that need major version bumps to match .NET 11. Review the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/migration) for any breaking changes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"08bb8c72-874a-4134-a699-e39c1e9efa2c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to search their codebase since they've described the files. Let me provide concise guidance.","outputTokens":316,"requestId":"6806:1CF7FE:109B5D0:14F2896:69FFE314"},"id":"7eb5b51e-8326-4cea-8011-c6747f57efcb","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:44:59.224Z","parentId":"77c8362c-2fad-4541-b364-3cd26501efbf"}
